property.value: This gate blocks off the entrance to the estate. It only opens after [[Starlo]] and [[Ed]] unlock it towards the end of the [[Pacifist Route]].

property.name: description
property.value: [[Martlet]] prevents [[Clover]] from walking off track. They can only move past this point after watching [[Chujin]]'s tapes.

property.name: description
property.value: A picture of [[Ceroba]], [[Chujin]], and [[Kanako]] taken in the dining room. [[Ceroba Ketsukane/In Battle|Kanako's mask]] is visible in the background.

property.name: description
property.value: [[Ceroba]]'s many almost identical outfits are seen here. [[Chujin]]'s outfits are said to be behind hers. Notably, Chujin's zabuton and Ceroba's [[CafÃ© Dune]] waiter outfit are visible here. This is also the only part of the Ketsukane Estate's design that is identifiable as Ceroba's.

property.name: description
property.value: The entrance to [[Chujin]]'s study is under this kotatsu, through a trapdoor.

property.name: description
property.value: Early Axis prototypes are found around the study, but this face is most recognizable as his.

property.name: description
property.value: This television is where [[Martlet]] and [[Clover]] watch Chujin's video journals. Returning here and interacting with the television with the [[Videotape]] in Clover's inventory lets them watch it. This is also the location of a [[Fun Value#Chujin stare|Fun Event]].
